Here is a simple 1-minute scalping strategy many beginners use in crypto trading. It uses 3 indicators and works well on liquid pairs like Bitcoin / Tether or Ethereum / Tether. 

---
1-Minute Scalping Strategy (Beginner Friendly)
Indicators to add
1. EMA 9 (Exponential Moving Average)

2. EMA 21

3. RSI (Relative Strength Index)



---
 Buy Setup (Long)
Enter a buy trade when:
1. EMA 9 crosses above EMA 21

2. Price is above both EMAs

3. RSI between 50–70

4. Volume starts increasing


 Target profit: 0.3% – 0.8% Stop-loss: just below the last candle low

---
 Sell Setup (Short)
Enter a sell trade when:
1. EMA 9 crosses below EMA 21

2. Price is below both EMAs

3. RSI between 30–50

4. Volume increases


 Target profit: 0.3% – 0.8% Stop-loss: above the last candle high

---
The 3 Indicators Explained
1. EMA 9
Shows very short-term trend
Reacts quickly to price changes

2. EMA 21
Shows slightly longer trend
Confirms the direction

3. RSI
Shows overbought or oversold conditions
Helps avoid entering late


